---
import Chapter from '../../layouts/Chapter.astro';
const lds = [{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Neighborhoods", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Wilmette", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods/wilmette"}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Place", "name": "Wilmette, Illinois", "url": "https://patrick.realestate/neighborhoods/wilmette", "containedInPlace": {"@type": "Place", "name": "North Shore, Chicago, IL"}}];
---
<Chapter
  title="Wilmette — Patrick Milhaupt · North Shore"
  description="Wilmette village brief — vintage brick, modern teardown-rebuilds, a walkable village core, and the most accessible entry point on the North Shore corridor."
  path="/neighborhoods/wilmette" current="/neighborhoods" palette="0.15"
  jsonLd={lds.length>=1 ? lds[0] : null}
  rail={[{"id": "ch-00", "num": "00", "label": "Opening"}, {"id": "ch-01", "num": "01", "label": "Snapshot"}, {"id": "ch-02", "num": "02", "label": "Architecture"}, {"id": "ch-03", "num": "03", "label": "Begin"}]}
>


  <section class="chapter" id="ch-00" data-chapter="0" data-palette="0.15">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="hashmark"><i></i></span>
        <div class="meta" style="border:0; padding:0;">
          <span class="eyebrow">Wilmette &middot; North Shore</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h1 class="headline" data-headline="">
        The corridor's <em>entry</em> point.
      </h1>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Wilmette is the most accessible <em>gateway</em> to the North Shore corridor &mdash; a walkable core, a layered mix of vintage and rebuilt housing stock, and the same New Trier feeder pattern as Winnetka and Kenilworth. It moves faster than any other village on the corridor.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn" href="#ch-01">View the snapshot &darr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/intelligence#ch-02">Open live dashboard</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-01" data-chapter="1" data-palette="0.40">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">01</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter One</span>
          <span class="sub">Wilmette Snapshot</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        A village of <em>access</em>, walkability, and velocity.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Wilmette's median list price of $1.18M is the lowest among the New Trier feeder villages, making it the most-cited gateway for families targeting that school district. Days-on-market run just 18 &mdash; the fastest on the corridor &mdash; and the sale-to-list ratio of 99.4% signals buyers competing into well-priced inventory. Price-per-square-foot of $432 reflects both the smaller average lot and the higher proportion of older, un-renovated housing stock that still trades within the village.
      </p>
      <div class="kpi-grid">
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Median Price</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$1.18M</span><span class="d">Most accessible feeder-village price</span></div>
        <div class="kpi pop"><span class="l">Days on Market</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">18 days</span><span class="d up">Fastest in the corridor</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">SP/OLP</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">99.4%</span><span class="d up">Buyers competing into inventory</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">$/SqFt</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$432</span><span class="d">Reflects mixed building stock</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="market-blend" style="padding:16px 24px 56px;">
  <div style="max-width:1120px;margin:0 auto;background:#0A1838;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);border-radius:16px;padding:22px 22px 12px;box-shadow:0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.35);">
    <div id="blendedMarket"></div>
  </div>
</section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-02" data-chapter="2" data-palette="0.65">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">02</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter Two</span>
          <span class="sub">Architecture &amp; Schools</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Layered <em>vocabulary</em>, anchor schools.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Wilmette's building stock is the corridor's most stylistically layered &mdash; a deep base of <strong>vintage brick from the 1920s and 1930s</strong>, a meaningful cohort of mid-century homes, and a steadily growing share of <strong>modern teardown-rebuilds</strong> on the eastern blocks closer to the lake. The village core around Central Avenue is genuinely walkable, with restaurants, shops, and the Metra station all within a short stroll, and the eastern beach blocks command a clear premium.
      </p>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Wilmette's K&ndash;8 students attend <strong>Wilmette District 39</strong>, which feeds into <strong>New Trier Township High School (District 203)</strong> &mdash; the same anchor district that serves Winnetka, Kenilworth, and Glencoe. The combination of New Trier access at a lower entry price is the single most important driver of Wilmette's velocity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-03" data-chapter="3" data-palette="1.00">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="num">03</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Begin</span>
          <span class="sub">A 30-minute call</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Move in <em>Wilmette</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Thirty minutes. We'll walk through the eastern-blocks versus core-village pricing differential, the velocity dynamic, and an honest three-to-six month forward read. No pitch.
      </p>
      <div class="begin-block fade-up">
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Direct</div><div class="v"><a href="tel:+18478499828" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;">(847) 849-9828</a></div></div>
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Email</div><div class="v"><a href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com</a></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center; margin-top: 32px;">
        <a class="btn" href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">Schedule the Call &rarr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/neighborhoods">Back to neighborhoods</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(lds[1])} />
  <script slot="scripts" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/7.9.0/d3.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script slot="scripts" src="/brand/charts/d3-brand.js" is:inline></script>
</Chapter>
